When `drift todo` runs and there exist one or more non-deleted markers with no links, the output appends a one-line summary warning after the sync/drift summary. The warning reads "N unlinked marker(s) found — run `drift list` to review." with singular "marker" when N=1 and plural "markers" when N>1. Unlinked markers are treated as actionable drift: todo exits 1 when unlinked markers exist, even if no edges have drifted (exit 0 means all specs are linked AND all edges are in sync). This makes `drift todo` safe as a CI gate — unlinked markers represent unfinished coverage work. The warning is suppressed in the "Nothing to check: no specs or markers registered." case (when both specs and markers are empty). Deleted markers (no longer on disk) are not counted as unlinked. See principles.friction.